Thieves escaped with thousands of pounds after blowing the front off a cash machine by pumping it full of gas. 

Notes and wreckage were left littering the road after the blast at the HSBC branch in Brislington, Bristol at 2.30am today. 

The gas had reportedly been pumped into the machine to cause an explosion which blew off the front. 

