Police are hunting a number of men in dark clothing and examining CCTV. 

An Avon and Somerset Police spokesman said: 'An investigation has begun to establish what happened.

'Some money was left lying on the ground. We don't know how much was taken.'

Detective Inspector Andy Gyther, speaking on how much was taken, added: 'It was a substantial amount, probably in the tens of thousands of pounds.' 

A HSBC spokesman said: 'We can confirm there was an attack on our ATM at the Brislington branch in Bristol and we are working closely with the police.'  

